This paper deals with the classification of tweets based on their content and metadata, which falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR), making cs.CL and cs.IR the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of classifiers to identify autogenerated tweets, which involves machine learning and data mining techniques, making cs.SI and cs.SD also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the issue of spam detection, which falls under the domain of computer security (cs.CR), making it a possible sub-category as well.
